JBR-4476 move TC build steps to scripts and Dockerfile (xenial-based)

ref JBR-4484

(cherry picked from commit 9ea01c581ee14ac0def2979303f897922760a76d)
JBR-4476 adapt environment to JBR 11
f Dockerfile
[IR][tests] More precise IrLinkageError checks

[IR][tests] Add tests for removal-of-abstract-fun IR linkage case

^KT-50771
[IR][tests] Add tests for IR linkage issues related to properties

[IR] Fix removal-of-abstract-fun IR linkage case

^KT-50771
Add new internal annotation `IntrinsicConstEvaluation` to kotlin-native
Mark all declarations that will be evaluated with ir interpreter

[JS] Manually change receiver's type of Char's equals method

Char's equals method in js doesn't work properly because now equals
method is not fake override in Char, but it is actual override and so
when we call equals for some char in js, it will not be boxed. To fix
it we need to get correct receiver's type.
[FIR] Allow constant values for IntrinsicConstEvaluation declarations
Add `IntrinsicConstEvaluation` annotation to some ir builtins functions
Add `ONLY_INTRINSIC_CONST` evaluation mode
Support interpretation of `trimMargin` and `trimIndent`
Allow interpreting `code` extension property
Add lowering that will evaluate all intrinsic const expressions
Update test data after introducing `IntrinsicConstEvaluation` annotation

Create `getInnerDeclarations` function to extract statements from parent

This function is needed to be able to work with files and scripts

Move string concat folding into `FlattenStringConcatenationLowering`

Originally `FoldConstantLowering` is responsible for this, but it can
be removed in the future.
Add tests to check constant evaluation for intrinsic const declarations
Add new diagnostic tests to check new rules for const modifier
Add jvm diagnostic tests to check report of exceptions from interpreter
Change ir const checker to match new rules of `IntrinsicConstEvaluation`

Add a flag to disable the DocumentCompiler #SCL-18946 #SCL-20219

- Hidden behind the registry toggle `scala.highlighting.compilation.document.compiler.enabled`
- If disabled, also disables compilation on project open

pull_request.title: Add IMT Nord Europe to supported domains
pull_request.body:
Hi JetBrains team!

Could you please add the IMT Nord Europe French high school to the educational institutions list?
Here are the useful information to help you validate this request:
* Domain being added: *imt-nord-europe.fr*
* Official website: https://imt-nord-europe.fr/en/
* URL to the IT-related courses offered:
  * General engineering: https://imt-nord-europe.fr/en/trainings-directory/general-engineering/
  * Telecom and IT Engineer: https://imt-nord-europe.fr/en/trainings-directory/telecommunications-and-it-engineer/
* Proof for the email domain name:
  * Attached: the Teacher's guide provided by the institution. Sorry, it's in French, it would need translating.
    [FOR_Guide-enseignant.pdf](https://github.com/JetBrains/swot/files/8717577/FOR_Guide-enseignant.pdf)
    
    The interesting part is in the middle of the second page:
    > In any case, as a teacher or speaker for the benefit of our training, you have an address such as @imt-nord-europe.fr or @ext.imt-nord-europe.fr. This address is your key that provides access to your My Services portal.

Thank you for all!

Have a nice day.

Eric.
